The paper deals with the Multiple-Input-Multiple-Output (MIMO) Broadcast Channel (BC) and Interference Channel (IC), which are topics related to Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of Rate-Splitting approach, which is a common technique used in Network Information Theory (cs.NI). The paper also deals with the use of Space-Time transmission, which is a topic related to Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the achievable Degrees-of-Freedom (DoF) regions, which is a topic related to Computer Engineering (cs.CE).
